Regarding estimation, most of the fixed-effects parameter estimates were approximately similar across all methods. Figure 3 also shows how the INLAjoint and R2WinBUGS closely and accurately approximated the posterior marginals of the fixed effects parameters. While the slightly wider spread of the MCMC curves observed in Fig. 3 indicates that it captures a bit more uncertainty in parameter estimation compared to INLA, the overall similarity confirms that INLA also offers a reliable approximation for Bayesian inference in the joint modeling of competing risks and skewed longitudinal data. However, substantial variations were observed in the estimates of the fixed effects of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
